{# FUNCTIONALITY IMPORTS #}
{% import "organisms/SitePreloader.njk" as Preloader %}
{% import "organisms/header/global-header.njk" as Header with context %}
{% import "organisms/footer/global-footer.njk" as Footer with context %}

{# UX IMPORTS #}
{% import "organisms/navigation/skip-links-nav.njk" as SkipLinksNav %}
{% import "molecules/background/sizzle-background.njk" as Background %}

{# SECTION CONTENT #}
{% import "organisms/section/hero.njk" as heroSection %}
{% import "organisms/section/bio.njk" as bioSection %}
{% import "organisms/section/awards.njk" as awardsSection %}
{% import "organisms/section/work.njk" as projectsSection %}
{% import "organisms/section/organizations.njk" as organizationsSection %}

{%- set projects = cms.home[0].featuredProjects -%}
{%- set awards = collections.awards -%}
{%- set organizations = collections.organizations -%}

{# SECTION STYLING #}
{% set sharedClasses = "" %}
{# Note that content values are set in frontmatter #}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<!-- Russell S. Lebo — Creative Technologist russell@dataink.io · dataink.io

This portfolio is built end-to-end: content modeled in Sanity Studio (TypeScript schemas), design tokens synced from
Figma, templates authored in Nunjucks (Eleventy), styling with Tailwind v4, and a custom GSAP choreography system that
handles scroll animation, section sequencing, and prefers-reduced-motion fallbacks across every animated element.

A few things the source demonstrates: · Semantic HTML with correct heading hierarchy and landmark structure — not
retrofitted · Progressive enhancement — content and structure are intact without JS; motion enhances · Atomic design
system (atoms → molecules → organisms → templates → pages) · Documented decisions — ADRs, co-located .md sidecars, and
a context authority model
    make intent traceable without asking

If you're a developer or designer reviewing this as part of a hiring decision: the structure, naming, and documentation
here reflect how I work on a team — clear, explicit, and built for the person who has to maintain it next. -->
<html lang="en" class="bg-slate-950">
  {% include "templates/partials/head.njk" %}
  <body>
    {% include "templates/partials/gtm-noscript.njk" %}
    {# {{ SkipLinksNav.render({ items: ["hero", "introduction", "recognition", "work", "organizations", "contact"] }) }} #}
    {{ Header.render({classes: 'bg-transparent font-display text-white'}) }}
    {{ Preloader.render({ kind: "spinner", message: "Lubricating the framistan…" }) }}
    {{ Background.render({
            id:"background",
            videoSrc: hero.videoSrc,
            defer: false,
            preload: "none",
            autoPlay: true
            }) }}
    <main id="page-main" aria-busy="true" class="mx-auto px-0 md:px-6 lg:px-12 col-span-full grid grid-cols-12">
      <div id="page-main-content" class="col-span-full">
        {# Note that content values are set in frontmatter #}
        {# The id param has a matching value in SELECTORS.js for consistency w/choreography during runtime #}
        {%- set heroLogo = cms.siteSettings[0].brand.logo.asset.url | inlineSvgFromUrl -%}
        {{ heroSection.render( { id: "hero", tagline: hero.tagline, logo: heroLogo, classes: sharedClasses}) }}
        {{ bioSection.render({ id: "introduction", copy: value, order: "1/5", classes: sharedClasses, buildDate: buildDate}) }}
        {{ projectsSection.render({ id: "work", copy: work, projects: projects, classes: sharedClasses, order: "3/5", buildDate: buildDate }) }}
      {{ awardsSection.render({ id: "recognition", copy: recognition, awards: awards, order: "2/5", classes: sharedClasses, buildDate: buildDate }) }}
    </div>
    </main>
    {# Contact form is rendered site-wide by the global footer. #}
    {{ Footer.render() }}
  {% include "templates/partials/choreography-script.njk" %}
</body></html>